                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/hist-301" class="program-course-title">
              HIST 301 U.S. Presidential Campaigning (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-27440" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: History and Classical Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      History              : The history of presidential campaigning in the U.S. will be considered against the backdrop of party change, technological development and the growth of American democracy.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              This course is not scheduled for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

